                <h1>The Essential Role of Cement in Construction</h1>
                <p>Cement, a fundamental construction material, is made from limestone and clay, heated to form clinker, which is ground into powder. It sets and hardens when mixed with water, making it crucial for concrete and masonry. Its versatility and strength make it essential in building foundations, roads, and infrastructure globally.</p>
